caption: I visit this spot a lot since I work in the area. I like how the customer service is always excellent and they keep the place well kept consistently. Pricing is affordable and they serve sizeable portions.
When I miss Lao food, I'd always order them from here. My favorites are: kao piak, sai ua, and moo ping, and sticky rice, of course!
~On point Thai with a very unique and evolving menu. One of my favorites in the TL Area. I haven't been disappointed with any dish that I have ever ordered. I highly recommend it.~
I had the small Tom Yum soup and the fried rice with crispy chicken, they were both very good, the service was cordial and the place was open to dine in. Clean place with plenty of hand sanitizer.
My best friend and I order from here anytime I'm over, and no matter what we get the food is delicious. The prices are great especially for San Francisco, and it really has the family sort of vibe.
So gooood

Yesterday was our first time we visited this good restaurant. But It is definitely not the last time. We had great time with the good service, with the excellent cooking and wine and with the friendly charge. We will no doubt return there soon.
The taste of Bangkok. Friendly staffs. Everything was just perfect.
I absolutely enjoyed their dishes and service, awesome location very close to my house. The workers are always helpful. Will come visit again.
A quaint Thai restaurant that's affordable. Food is decent.

Very well organised and convenient place. They serve generous portions and for reasonable prices. I loved the food very much and the staff members were very welcoming and informative. Will definitely recommend this spot.

Food was cooked with care and quality. Enjoyed the tom yum soup and pad ped stiryfry but the portions were too tiny for the price. Nice interiors with a TV, seems like a nice place to kickback with some beers (they have Chang!).

Tycoon is great - definitely try the Lao specialties like the Sai Ua and Gai Yang. Curries have been great too - if you want it truly spicy you can ask for it "thai hot" and they will accommodate. Surprisingly good beer selection as well - Tycoon also offers great lunch and happy hour specials.
We usually order from here to Uber eats. We’ve tried a couple but our favorite is Pad See You by far! Flat noodles with broccoli, meat and other veggies. Amazing! We love it!

One of my top spots for tasty thai food. very appetizing. the service was very sociable and kind. the bill was good for what you get.
Thai food, my favorite treat. certainly a top place in the area. i had a cousin come into town and asked me to take him back here. this place has a nice design.
Love everything about Tycoon Thai Restaurant. The staff is wonderful and the items are all so well chosen. I love making charcuterie and cheese plates for date nights at home.
